# Project Structure Guide

This is a Next.js 15 project with TypeScript, using modern React features and a comprehensive UI component library.

## Main Directories

- `app/`: Contains the main application routes and layouts using Next.js App Router
  - `(www)/`: Main website routes
  - `layout.tsx`: Root layout component
  - `globals.css`: Global styles

- `components/`: Reusable UI components organized by feature
  - `ui/`: Base UI components
  - `chat/`: Chat-related components
  - `comprehensive-data/`: Data visualization components
  - `profile/`: User profile components
  - `exchange/`: Exchange-related components
  - `news/`: News feed components
  - `board/`: Board-related components
  - `trading/`: Trading interface components
  - `user/`: User management components

- `hooks/`: Custom React hooks
- `lib/`: Utility functions and shared logic
- `providers/`: React context providers
- `public/`: Static assets

## Key Technologies

- Next.js 15 with App Router
- React 19
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS
- Radix UI components
- React Hook Form with Zod validation
- TanStack Table
- Recharts for data visualization

## Development

- Use `pnpm` as the package manager
- Development server: `pnpm dev`
- Build: `pnpm build`
- Start production: `pnpm start`
- Lint: `pnpm lint`


- Do Not Write Comments
- Do Not use HardCoded Colors
- If you are not sure, stop and ask
- Use PNPM please

